2. Our application needs permission to have access to your:
2.1.
Storage:
We need
access
to your Storage to install the Application. Further, we need access to your device storage in order to add the audio files in the playlist available in the Application or created by you in our app
.
You have options to filter out the unwanted short audio files from the playlist and therefore the Application needs to have access to your storage. This permission is also needed to install the Application in the storage.
2.2.
Network Communication/access and Wi-Fi:
We continuously let our users have the best experience while using our Application. We invest a considerable amount of time fixing errors and improving the functionalities of the Applications. Whenever we add a new feature or fix an error, we intimate our users about the updates. We also need
network
details to optimize the services on slow networks.
2.3.
Audio Settings and Reading the Contents of Your Storage:
The Application allows you to edit the info of the audio files such as the name of the audio file, details of the artist and album. You can also delete unwanted files using the Application. Therefore this permission is needed.
2.4.
Device and App Information:
In order to detect the crashes and recover the Application to its state we need to know your device status,
operating system, and its version, hardware model, mobile network's unique device identifier
etc
.
2.5.
Device id, Phone Status:
All the user logs, crash reports, performance reports, and analytic logs are mapped under unique user ids. All the
