2.9: Contact Permission: To set the ringtone for any person in the contact list, this permission is required.
2.10: Playlists and Application settings Backup: Audify
Music Player collects, transmits and stores details of audio files added to your playlist to restore playlists after reinstallation along with application settings on Audify Cloud. Audify
Music Player collects, transmits and stores this by default to provide a better experience.
3. Cookies:
Cookies are small text files designed to identify your preferences and manage your sessions. They are transferred via web servers and are stored in your storage. They help the Application remember the language you have selected or the times you have opened the Application and the user id, date, and time you have visited. We do not seek permission for Third-Party cookies. You can disable and delete the cookies at your convenience. However, disabling the cookies may lead to the Application not functioning correctly.
4. Personal and Sensitive Data
4.1. Images -
Audify
Music Player collects, transmits and stores images when you create Audify Mix and add images for that created mix on Audify Cloud. We do not collect your images by default and it be collected only when you create and add images to the Mix feature in the application.
4.2. Audios
- Audify
Music Player collects, transmits and stores audio when you add audio to the Audify Mix feature on Audify Cloud. We do not collect, transmit or store your audio by default and it be collected only when add audio to the Mix feature in the application.
4.2. Name -
Audify
Music Player collects, transmits and stores names once you log in or create Audify Mix to provide a more personal experience in the Application on Audify Cloud.
